<assessmentItem xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqti_v2p1" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqti_v2p1 http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/qti/qtiv2p1/imsqti_v2p1p1.xsd http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML http://www.w3.org/Math/XMLSchema/mathml2/mathml2.xsd" identifier="id1848fd6b-84f7-487e-a261-015b5eb8d88c" title="RadiusConvergenceProperties" adaptive="false" timeDependent="false"><responseDeclaration identifier="RESPONSE_1" cardinality="multiple" baseType="identifier"><correctResponse><value>idb7e0d16a-e398-440d-b756-2614384b150a</value><value>id26208b8a-bfb6-4a5e-8376-2ad7c8003ab4</value><value>id9a6f06ea-31d9-46c8-883f-ac57f9bf51a8</value><value>id2d23196b-33f9-414a-a6a3-3732db239c37</value><value>id07833a8a-e037-426a-b326-995624f38d7e</value></correctResponse></responseDeclaration><outcomeDeclaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" baseType="float"><defaultValue><value>0</value></defaultValue></outcomeDeclaration><outcomeDeclaration identifier="MAXSCORE" cardinality="single" baseType="float"><defaultValue><value>3</value></defaultValue></outcomeDeclaration><outcomeDeclaration identifier="FEEDBACKBASIC" cardinality="single" baseType="identifier"><defaultValue><value>empty</value></defaultValue></outcomeDeclaration><itemBody ><p>Mark each true assertion about the<strong> radius </strong>\( r\)<strong> of convergence</strong> of a complex power series  $$ \sum_{k=0}^{\infty } a_k (z-z_0)^k $$ about the point \( z_0 \in \mathbb C\).</p><p> </p><choiceInteraction responseIdentifier="RESPONSE_1" shuffle="false" maxChoices="0"><simpleChoice identifier="idb7e0d16a-e398-440d-b756-2614384b150a"><p>The radius \(r\) of convergence is not affected by omitting a finite amount of terms \( a_k\) of the series.</p></simpleChoice><simpleChoice identifier="id26208b8a-bfb6-4a5e-8376-2ad7c8003ab4"><p>\( \frac{1}{r}  =  \lim\ sup_{k\to \infty} \sqrt[k]{|a_k|} \)</p></simpleChoice><simpleChoice identifier="idfc89a61f-c18c-4d1b-b31a-93f8ed216e75"><p>The series converges for each z with \( |z-z_0| \le r \) and the series diverges for each z with \( |z-z_0| \gt r\).</p></simpleChoice><simpleChoice identifier="id9a6f06ea-31d9-46c8-883f-ac57f9bf51a8"><p>The series converges for each z with \( |z-z_0| \lt r\) and the series diverges for each z with \( |z-z_0| \gt r\).</p></simpleChoice><simpleChoice identifier="id830bdd90-a082-4afe-ba81-b7349cad03a9"><p>\[ r = \lim_{k \to \infty} \frac{a_k}{a_{k+1}}\]</p></simpleChoice><simpleChoice identifier="id2d23196b-33f9-414a-a6a3-3732db239c37"><p>The series converges absolutely for every z with \( |z -z_0| \lt r \).</p></simpleChoice><simpleChoice identifier="idbe36c894-a11f-4aab-8de4-162aa8a78300"><p>If the series is converging, then \( | z- z_0 | \lt r \) must hold.</p></simpleChoice><simpleChoice identifier="id07833a8a-e037-426a-b326-995624f38d7e"><p>The series is complex differentiable for all z with \( |z-z_0| \lt r \) </p></simpleChoice></choiceInteraction></itemBody><responseProcessing><responseCondition><responseIf><isNull><variable identifier="RESPONSE_1" /></isNull><setOutcomeValue identifier="FEEDBACKBASIC"><baseValue baseType="identifier">empty</baseValue></setOutcomeValue></responseIf><responseElseIf><match><variable identifier="RESPONSE_1" /><correct identifier="RESPONSE_1" /></match><setOutcomeValue identifier="SCORE"><sum><variable identifier="SCORE" /><variable identifier="MAXSCORE" /></sum></setOutcomeValue><setOutcomeValue identifier="FEEDBACKBASIC"><baseValue baseType="identifier">correct</baseValue></setOutcomeValue></responseElseIf><responseElse><setOutcomeValue identifier="FEEDBACKBASIC"><baseValue baseType="identifier">incorrect</baseValue></setOutcomeValue></responseElse></responseCondition></responseProcessing></assessmentItem>
